HEADWORD: Oryx
<hw>O"ryx</hw> <pr>(⟦omac⟧"r⟦icr⟧ks)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos>
<ety>[NL., from Gr. <grk>'o`ryx</grk> a kind of gazelle or
antelope.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of African antelopes
which includes the gemsbok, the leucoryx, the bisa antelope (<spn>Oryx
beisa</spn>), and the beatrix antelope (<spn>Oryx beatrix</spn>) of
Arabia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

